						<div class="postbody"><div class="quotetitle">Bregalad wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">In my opinion, using 32kb bank is crazy in most cases, except if you're doing very tricky tricks, and I'll think to only use 16kb banks if I were you. I really ask how most Rare games does to use only 32kb bankswitching.</div>
<br />GNROM, BNROM, and the Color Dreams board also have 32 KB PRG bankswitching. As long as you're not using DMC, it's easy to work around the bankswitching limitation using jump tables in RAM or jump tables duplicated through the last 1 KB of each PRG bank.</div>

