					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">Yeah, it is do-able, but it still is much easier to work with one hardwired bank, I think. 32kb banks maybe allow you to place all data and code related together in the same bank.
<br />For example, you'll have 32kb with all maps and all code that do something with the maps, 32kb with all music and you music replay code, 32kb with all text of the games and all programm that shows text, etc...
<br />If you want more than 32kb, you'll have to be very tricky.
<br />In a standard configuration, you'd rather have data in the bankswitched part and code in the hardwired place, OR have both code and data bankswitched.</div>

					
