			<td valign="top">
				<table width="100%" cellspacing="5">
				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">No, it's because the SUROM board is wired differently, such that the CHR high address pins go to PRG instead of CHR.
<br />
<br />CHR RAM games using the MMC1 can be reconstructed from iNES files as follows: <ul><li>Mapper 1, no CHR ROM, PRG ROM 16-256 KB =&gt; SNROM </li><li>Mapper 1, no CHR ROM, PRG ROM 512 KB =&gt; SUROM </li></ul></div>

					<br clear="all" /><br />

						<table width="100%" cellspacing="0">
						<tr valign="middle">
							<td class="gensmall" align="right">
							
							</td>
						</tr>
						</table>
					</td>
				</tr>
				</table>
			</td>
